HB 310 Original 2026 Regular Session Carlson
Abstract: Provides for the reassignment of a defendant's case when the right to a jury trial
has been waived.
Present law provides for the right of a defendant to waive a jury trial.
Proposed law retains present law.
Proposed law requires the random reassignment of a defendant's case among all the
remaining judges who are assigned criminal matters within their divisions or sections
immediately following the filing of the defendant's motion pursuant to present law in a
district court with three or more judges who are assigned criminal matters.
Proposed law authorizes the district attorney to file a motion to waive reassignment of the
defendant's case within 10 days of the granting of a motion to waive trial by jury. Further
requires the district court to grant any motion to waive reassignment.
(Amends C.Cr.P. Art. 780(B))
